commit_message:
Create bedpe2washu.sh

This script process a file in bedpe format and produce a pair of bed.gz and bed.gz.tbi files to display the data on WashU epigenome browser under the long-range interaction data.

Create bed2rf2matrix.sh

Script to map a set of peaks files (in bed format) to the genomic coordinates of an enzyme's restriction fragments and then, construct a whole matrix of binary TFBS events.

Create heatmaps_sorted_by_peaks.m

This MATLAB script will take a set of matrices (as the ones generated by BED2matrix.sh) and will plot a heatmap for each file. It will sort the histones in descending order according to the heights of the peaks, provided in a separated file. It will also plot a heatmap with the number of Reads-in-Peaks (RiP) from the peaks file and will add an empty row in the histone profile if it doesn't have nothing at this genomic region.

Create heatmaps_sorted_by_histones_fold_change.m

This MATLAB script will take a set of matrices (as the ones generated by BED2matrix.sh) and will plot a heatmap for each file. It will sort the histones in descending order according to the fold change of two given histones. It will also plot a heatmap with the number of Reads-in-Peaks (RiP) from a given peaks file and will add an empty row in the histone profile if it doesn't have nothing at this genomic region.

Create BED2matrix.sh

This script uses the annotation tool from HOMER to generate a histogram from a ChIP-Seq experiment. It will uses the BED and a bigwig files from a histone experiment to generate a matrix with the number of counts around the regions defined in a given peaks file.

First commit

This script will compute the Fraction of Reads-in-Peaks (FRiP, see PubMed 22955991) for all peaks file in the current folder. It requires to be have the original file with the aligned reads, in BED format, into the same folder.
